WEBVTT

00:01.235 --> 00:02.468
Margaret: Merry christmas.

00:02.603 --> 00:04.169
♪♪♪

00:05.239 --> 00:06.972
- Agh.
(hard slap)

00:07.107 --> 00:09.842
(melancholy "jingle bells"
plays)

00:12.446 --> 00:14.079
- (remorseful exhale)

00:14.081 --> 00:15.981
- We lived every day in fear...

00:16.050 --> 00:18.784
With this little bomb next
to us, that...

00:18.919 --> 00:20.652
<i> - (maniacal laughter)</i>
<i> - we loved so much,</i>

00:20.788 --> 00:23.121
<i> Was gonna go off</i>
<i> and destroy everything.</i>

00:23.190 --> 00:25.591
- Oh, my god.
(cookies clatter, tray clangs)

00:27.928 --> 00:30.328
♪♪♪

00:30.330 --> 00:32.931
♪ whoa-ohhh! Yeaahh! ♪

00:34.535 --> 00:37.736
♪ we've hung the ornaments
with care ♪

00:40.007 --> 00:42.808
♪ it's christmastime,
my dear ♪

00:42.810 --> 00:44.243
(echoey shaky breathing)

00:47.915 --> 00:50.148
♪ the snow has
fallin' now ♪

00:50.217 --> 00:53.485
♪ and it's finally time
to tuck-in the kids ♪

00:54.755 --> 00:57.289
♪ it's time to celebrate ♪

00:57.291 --> 00:59.858
♪ all the blessings
of this day ♪

00:59.860 --> 01:01.626
- Oh!
(bucket clatters)

01:01.662 --> 01:04.096
♪ singing songs and
spreading christmas cheer ♪

01:05.499 --> 01:08.099
♪ ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh ♪

01:08.135 --> 01:10.435
♪ kissing under mistletoe ♪

01:10.504 --> 01:12.438
(ornaments smash)
- oh!

01:13.774 --> 01:16.141
♪ at least one thing is clear ♪

01:16.143 --> 01:18.710
Ahhhhh!

01:18.746 --> 01:21.179
(christmas music turns eerie)

01:21.248 --> 01:23.615
<i> (shrill screaming)</i>

01:24.651 --> 01:26.185
(sobbing)
(water sloshes)

01:26.187 --> 01:28.087
<i> (door slams shut)</i>

01:28.222 --> 01:30.522
(heavy breathing)

01:30.657 --> 01:32.591
<i> (approaching footsteps thud)</i>

01:32.660 --> 01:34.659
What, what are you doing here?

01:34.728 --> 01:36.261
(heavy breathing)

01:37.331 --> 01:41.733
Donovan: Caleb. Caleb.
Officer: Last one is clear.

01:41.802 --> 01:43.535
- Caleb, this is the police.

01:43.537 --> 01:46.405
If you're in here,
identify yourself.

01:46.407 --> 01:49.007
<i> Officer: Caleb!</i>
<i> This is the police!</i>

01:49.076 --> 01:51.476
(melancholy "jingle bells"
plays)

01:51.479 --> 01:53.479
<i> Officer: That is clear!</i>

01:54.548 --> 01:56.781
(police radio chatter)

01:56.851 --> 02:03.421
♪♪♪

02:03.423 --> 02:05.257
(drawer rumbles)

02:05.392 --> 02:12.096
♪♪♪

02:12.133 --> 02:13.698
(police radio chatter)

02:13.767 --> 02:15.901
Donovan: Caleb?

02:15.970 --> 02:18.637
(footsteps thud)

02:19.773 --> 02:21.673
This is the police.

02:25.479 --> 02:31.383
♪♪♪

02:31.518 --> 02:34.486
(slithering sound)

02:36.790 --> 02:39.458
(eerie "jingle bells"
continues)

02:39.593 --> 02:41.927
(slithering)

02:46.000 --> 02:51.803
♪♪♪

02:51.805 --> 02:53.272
(steps thud)

02:54.341 --> 03:00.812
♪♪♪

03:00.814 --> 03:02.281
(slithering sounds)

03:05.519 --> 03:07.185
- Sheesh!

03:07.254 --> 03:10.022
♪♪♪

03:12.693 --> 03:16.862
♪♪♪

03:19.433 --> 03:21.566
(fire crackles)
- (shaky breathing)

03:21.569 --> 03:23.702
<i> (door opens and shuts)</i>

03:26.340 --> 03:28.307
(footsteps crunch)

03:30.511 --> 03:32.177
- Oh, god.

03:36.217 --> 03:37.782
- I never thought
this through.

03:37.851 --> 03:40.219
- Don't. Don't. Don't.

03:41.555 --> 03:43.488
- You haven't seen me
in such a long time.

03:43.624 --> 03:45.857
- Yeah, I haven't seen you
since katie died.

03:48.562 --> 03:50.829
- I didn't leave
because of you.

03:50.898 --> 03:53.331
- Well, I killed katie,
and then you left,

03:53.400 --> 03:55.334
So yeah, yeah,
I think you did.

03:56.970 --> 03:58.736
- I never blamed you
for katie's death.

03:58.772 --> 04:00.539
- Really? Really?
Then, why did you leave?

04:00.674 --> 04:02.741
Hmm?

04:02.810 --> 04:04.476
Why did you leave?

04:04.611 --> 04:06.278
- Because I couldn't stay.

04:06.280 --> 04:08.580
- Oh you...
You couldn't stay.

04:10.951 --> 04:12.684
Well, there's that.

04:14.321 --> 04:16.754
- Jenny.

04:16.790 --> 04:18.957
Jenny. Okay.

04:21.828 --> 04:23.895
- Don't.

04:23.897 --> 04:25.631
(shaky breathing)

04:26.634 --> 04:29.634
- Do you know that
when you were a baby,

04:29.703 --> 04:31.703
You had colic.

04:32.840 --> 04:34.639
For the first six months
of your life,

04:34.675 --> 04:36.642
You never slept for more
than 45 minutes.

04:37.845 --> 04:40.312
I rocked you and I held you,

04:40.381 --> 04:42.714
But the only thing that
would ever soothe you

04:42.849 --> 04:45.583
Was when gord would take you
in the car and...

04:45.619 --> 04:48.053
And drive up and down
the highway.

04:49.323 --> 04:51.623
He always had this magic
with you.

04:53.327 --> 04:54.926
He could always make (sniffs)

04:54.995 --> 04:56.962
Sunshine out of the darkest day.

05:00.534 --> 05:03.000
But after katie died,
I couldn't get out of bed,

05:03.037 --> 05:04.936
I couldn't look after myself.

05:06.740 --> 05:08.407
Let alone, you.

05:10.544 --> 05:13.211
I thought that you were better
off with your father.

05:13.213 --> 05:14.980
(engine roars)

05:19.953 --> 05:22.020
Can you forgive me?

05:25.326 --> 05:28.427
(sniffles)
- it's cold outside. Go in.

05:30.097 --> 05:31.763
- (sighs)

05:31.765 --> 05:33.532
- Please, go in.

05:34.768 --> 05:36.467
(engine shuts off)

05:36.503 --> 05:39.304
(truck door opens, closes)

05:41.442 --> 05:43.841
- Hey!
- Hey.

05:43.877 --> 05:46.778
- Oh, gordon didn't tell you
I was coming.

05:49.216 --> 05:50.715
- No, but um...

05:50.718 --> 05:52.250
- I'm so sorry,
I thought you knew it.

05:52.252 --> 05:54.119
He uh, he invited me
for the day.

05:54.121 --> 05:55.654
- Yeah, it's fine.

05:55.656 --> 05:57.456
Um, actually I'm uh, (sniffs)

05:58.525 --> 06:00.325
I'm kinda glad you're here.

06:00.460 --> 06:02.393
It's a, it's a bit
of gong show right now.

06:02.429 --> 06:04.763
- Oh.
- Sorry.

06:04.898 --> 06:06.865
Gordon: Hey, liam!
- Hey!

06:06.867 --> 06:08.667
- You made it. That's great!

06:09.670 --> 06:12.771
Oh, I gotta introduce you
to somebody.

06:14.208 --> 06:16.241
I want you to meet peggy.
- Hi.

06:16.243 --> 06:18.676
- It's jenny's mom.
It's a little awkward, okay,

06:18.712 --> 06:21.279
I know, but it's fine.
We're all here,

06:21.348 --> 06:23.481
We're gonna have
a fantastic feast.

06:23.550 --> 06:26.618
Just wanna know one thing,
do you like gravy?

06:26.687 --> 06:28.820
- I love gravy.

06:28.955 --> 06:30.689
- Okay, plenty of gravy,
I guess.

06:33.593 --> 06:36.228
(approaching engine rumbles)

06:37.264 --> 06:39.231
Liam: Who's that?

06:39.233 --> 06:40.699
- It's just, it's work.
I think.

06:40.701 --> 06:42.367
(door shuts)

06:44.271 --> 06:47.072
- Hey, clark.
What are you doin' here?

06:48.509 --> 06:52.376
- Here, uh, my mama never let
me come empty-handed, so,

06:52.413 --> 06:54.146
Happy holidays.

06:54.281 --> 06:56.781
- So, did my um,

06:56.784 --> 06:58.717
Did my dad invite you?

06:58.719 --> 07:00.351
- No, no, no,
I have some news.

07:00.387 --> 07:02.120
- Oh.
- Donovan didn't wanna call you,

07:02.189 --> 07:03.455
But I thought you'd
like to know,

07:03.590 --> 07:05.891
Caleb browning escaped
from the hospital.

07:06.026 --> 07:08.260
- What? When?
- This morning.

07:10.798 --> 07:13.064
- Wow, okay. Um...

07:13.199 --> 07:14.832
- I just wanted to make sure
you're okay, you know,

07:14.868 --> 07:16.635
After what happened to you
yesterday.

07:17.805 --> 07:19.937
- Oh, right. Um...

07:19.973 --> 07:22.674
Yeah, no,
I'm-I'm-I'm-I'm okay.

07:22.809 --> 07:24.843
I'm okay.

07:26.346 --> 07:29.681
- I got your voicemail.
- Right. Um...

07:31.017 --> 07:32.950
Yeah, uh sorry, I just,
I just--

07:32.952 --> 07:34.285
- Uh, it's okay, it's okay.

07:34.321 --> 07:37.689
I'm not asking for anything
from you now.

07:37.824 --> 07:39.791
- (shaky inhale)
- okay.

07:39.793 --> 07:42.360
If you ever need me,

07:42.496 --> 07:44.429
You know where to find me.

07:47.835 --> 07:51.036
- Thanks. Thanks.

07:51.171 --> 07:53.304
(footsteps crunch)

07:53.373 --> 07:55.907
(box rattles)

07:55.976 --> 07:57.642
(door opens and shuts,
engine starts)

08:00.214 --> 08:02.180
(ornament jingles)

08:02.182 --> 08:05.316
♪♪♪

08:05.385 --> 08:07.853
(jenny's phone buzzes)

08:09.389 --> 08:11.456
(slithering sound)

08:11.458 --> 08:12.857
Jenny: Well,

08:12.860 --> 08:15.994
This is the longest tapeworm
I've ever seen.

08:15.996 --> 08:17.862
Donovan: This is the first
tapeworm I've ever seen,

08:17.865 --> 08:19.598
And it's more than enough
for me.

08:21.735 --> 08:25.403
- So, have any idea
where caleb is?

08:25.405 --> 08:28.006
- No. Still trying to piece
together

08:28.008 --> 08:29.741
How he got out of the psych
ward.

08:29.876 --> 08:32.611
Hey, so the tapeworm wriggled
out of her wound?

08:33.680 --> 08:35.680
- Yeah, looks like she was
stabbed.

08:35.716 --> 08:37.348
The wound cut her intestine,

08:37.384 --> 08:41.953
Which is where tapeworms
attach to their hosts.

08:42.022 --> 08:43.288
(snips)
- makes sense.

08:43.357 --> 08:45.090
The knife drawer was raided
and--

08:46.760 --> 08:48.760
- Yeah.

08:48.829 --> 08:50.895
- She was here cleaning.

08:51.965 --> 08:53.665
- I mean, why did she come back
to the house,

08:53.800 --> 08:56.468
Let alone to clean it?

08:58.238 --> 09:00.205
<i> None of this makes any sense.</i>

09:01.975 --> 09:03.407
(traffic whooshes)

09:03.443 --> 09:05.210
Jenny: Look, um,

09:05.345 --> 09:08.513
Caleb escaped from
the hospital.

09:08.515 --> 09:11.449
- I know. The police called me.

09:11.585 --> 09:13.852
Did they find him?

09:13.854 --> 09:16.054
- No. Uh,

09:16.056 --> 09:17.989
And his surrogate sister
was just found dead.

09:18.124 --> 09:20.058
- (exhales)

09:21.261 --> 09:23.128
That's awful.

09:23.263 --> 09:25.864
- (sighs) just, I don't think,
I don't think that he would--

09:27.000 --> 09:28.532
- You're having trouble
reconciling

09:28.569 --> 09:30.701
Your instincts about caleb.
- Yeah.

09:30.737 --> 09:33.471
Look, I just...
I really believed that,

09:33.473 --> 09:35.473
That he had lost his memory,
but if he,

09:35.609 --> 09:38.075
If he killed flora--

09:39.112 --> 09:41.879
- Someone can be both a victim
of trauma and an abuser.

09:42.916 --> 09:46.017
Maybe we saw one side of him
and this family sees the other.

09:46.152 --> 09:47.885
- Okay, but why cover for him,
if you're flora?

09:47.921 --> 09:50.187
You know, why clean up after
him if he just killed

09:50.223 --> 09:52.490
Two people that you love?

09:52.559 --> 09:54.559
- Because they love him.

09:55.696 --> 09:57.662
They're protecting him.

09:57.664 --> 09:59.698
(traffic whooshes)

10:02.502 --> 10:04.568
Jenny: They were trauma bonded,
donovan.

10:04.605 --> 10:06.838
I mean, it's when an,

10:06.907 --> 10:09.440
An abused person forms a strong
emotional attachment

10:09.476 --> 10:11.475
To their uh, to their abuser.

10:11.511 --> 10:13.778
Donovan: Flora and caleb?
- Yeah, think about it.

10:13.780 --> 10:16.914
I mean, flora had been abused
by caleb, for years.

10:16.984 --> 10:19.517
She even took the family's
hush money.

10:19.519 --> 10:22.087
<i> - So, she goes to clean up</i>
<i> after the murders?</i>

10:22.222 --> 10:24.922
- Well, maybe in her mind,
she was cleaning up after him,

10:24.958 --> 10:27.592
You know, protecting him,
like she has all these years.

10:27.727 --> 10:30.128
<i> - She might not be</i>
<i> the only one.</i>

10:30.197 --> 10:31.930
- What?

10:31.932 --> 10:33.598
<i> - We can't get hold</i>
<i> of aaron browning,</i>

10:33.733 --> 10:35.934
<i> And the address he gave us</i>
<i> is fake.</i>

10:36.069 --> 10:39.937
- Okay, um, I'll call you
if I find anything.

10:39.939 --> 10:44.342
♪♪♪

10:44.411 --> 10:46.277
(snipping sounds)

10:49.282 --> 10:53.418
♪♪♪

10:53.553 --> 10:55.520
River: (tired exhale)

10:58.759 --> 11:01.559
The tapeworm head is still
attached to her intestine.

11:01.628 --> 11:03.662
- I'd place her time of death
as early this morning.

11:03.797 --> 11:06.363
- I just wish we
had more to go on.

11:06.400 --> 11:08.199
- There's this.

11:14.107 --> 11:15.907
Jenny: Flora had liver cancer?

11:16.042 --> 11:18.343
- I found the same masses
on john browning's liver.

11:19.513 --> 11:21.278
I thought cancer too,
at first, but--

11:21.314 --> 11:23.448
- Then we got the results back
from the lab.

11:23.583 --> 11:25.650
They're cysts from the tapeworm
larvae.

11:25.785 --> 11:27.885
Jenny: They both had tapeworm?

11:27.887 --> 11:29.688
- We'll send these out
for biopsy.

11:31.058 --> 11:33.458
- Or we could just do this.

11:37.698 --> 11:40.064
(cyst oozes)

11:40.067 --> 11:41.666
Dennis: (disgusted) ugh!

11:41.668 --> 11:43.568
Jenny: Okay, yeah,
looks like anchovy paste.

11:45.405 --> 11:49.040
Oh, it's a classic descriptor
for tapeworm cysts.

11:50.210 --> 11:51.876
- Even I find that disgusting.

11:52.011 --> 11:54.111
- Did she have any cysts
in her brain?

11:54.147 --> 11:55.947
- No.

11:56.082 --> 11:57.949
- Um, look, you guys,

11:58.018 --> 11:59.884
You guys go home after this,
okay?

11:59.920 --> 12:02.020
River: We will.

12:02.022 --> 12:05.156
Happy holidays, jenny!
Dennis: Happy holidays, jenny.

12:05.158 --> 12:07.392
Jenny: Happy holidays, guys.

12:08.495 --> 12:10.027
Donovan: Sorry, what?

12:10.063 --> 12:12.363
Jenny: John browning and flora
both have cysts

12:12.365 --> 12:14.632
From old tapeworm infections.
- And?

12:14.768 --> 12:17.301
- What if the whole family
had tapeworm at some point?

12:17.370 --> 12:20.038
Tapeworm larvae can travel
to your-your organs

12:20.040 --> 12:22.774
And your muscles,
and they can cause cysts.

12:23.810 --> 12:27.512
So, I'm thinking that caleb
browning has tapeworm cysts

12:27.514 --> 12:30.114
In his brain. And if it's
in his frontal lobe,

12:30.183 --> 12:33.050
Then that would explain why
he can't control his emotions.

12:33.086 --> 12:34.986
- All right, then, why wouldn't
the rest of the family

12:35.121 --> 12:36.621
Be violent?
Why wouldn't aaron be?

12:36.756 --> 12:38.189
- Because it's incredibly rare

12:38.191 --> 12:39.991
For the cysts to travel
to your brain.

12:39.993 --> 12:41.526
- Hold on for a sec, jenny.

12:41.661 --> 12:43.061
- We got a list of properties
the brownings own.

12:43.196 --> 12:44.863
Places where caleb
could be hiding out.

12:44.865 --> 12:46.664
Closest is some land north
of pickering.

12:46.733 --> 12:48.666
- All right, thanks, man.
Hey, jenny?

12:48.735 --> 12:50.702
I think I might have a lead on
where caleb might be hiding.

12:50.837 --> 12:52.603
- Okay, I need to come with you.

12:52.739 --> 12:54.972
- Okay, jenny--
- yeah, donovan,

12:54.974 --> 12:56.775
I know he's dangerous,
but he's also sick,

12:56.910 --> 12:58.609
And if I can explain
that to him,

12:58.645 --> 13:01.145
I think he will accept help.
- All right, fine.

13:01.214 --> 13:02.881
I'll text you the address.

13:02.883 --> 13:04.783
- Okay, thank you.
I'll meet you there.

13:10.791 --> 13:13.558
- What if I had never left?
Hmm?

13:13.560 --> 13:15.960
What if I had been there
for jenny

13:15.996 --> 13:18.563
When she got her period,

13:18.565 --> 13:21.699
She went on her first date...

13:21.701 --> 13:23.902
When she got married.

13:23.904 --> 13:25.570
All those things,

13:25.572 --> 13:27.672
All those milestones
that I missed.

13:31.244 --> 13:33.511
And she doesn't want me here.

13:33.580 --> 13:35.547
- What?
Okay, you can't give up.

13:36.783 --> 13:38.683
I mean, you've gotta just...
You know,

13:39.919 --> 13:41.920
Keep on trying with her.

13:41.922 --> 13:44.389
Keep on knocking on that door.

13:46.526 --> 13:48.459
She's tough because
she's fragile.

13:48.594 --> 13:51.129
- Huh, well, that daughter of
yours

13:51.264 --> 13:53.464
Never got that right hook
from me.

13:53.500 --> 13:55.132
She has your temper.

13:55.168 --> 13:57.068
- Oh, no. Not mine.

13:57.070 --> 14:00.038
- Oh, definitely runs
in your side of the family.

14:02.943 --> 14:06.010
- Hm.
- You did a good job, gord.

14:06.046 --> 14:07.745
- I really tried, but I just,

14:07.814 --> 14:09.814
I felt like I didn't know what
I was doing half the time.

14:12.719 --> 14:14.686
- This isn't what I pictured,
you know.

14:16.690 --> 14:19.824
When we used to... Lie out
on your old ford mustang,

14:21.361 --> 14:23.561
Imagining what our life
was gonna look like.

14:25.565 --> 14:27.632
We were so young.

14:27.701 --> 14:30.368
- Oh, sweetheart.
- (crying)

14:36.610 --> 14:39.644
- There's absolutely never
been anyone for me, but you.

14:39.646 --> 14:41.512
Not anywhere.

14:41.548 --> 14:44.282
- (sighs, sniffles)

14:45.452 --> 14:45.984
- Just...

14:47.988 --> 14:49.654
It's just always been you.

14:49.656 --> 14:52.423
You know, I've imagined you
every single day?

14:53.927 --> 14:56.327
- Oh, well.
- You look so good.

14:56.396 --> 14:58.129
- I'm here.

14:58.198 --> 15:05.770
♪♪♪

15:06.806 --> 15:08.306
- Do you wanna go upstairs?

15:10.677 --> 15:12.877
- Oh, gord...

15:17.217 --> 15:19.217
- You can say no,
if you want to.

15:19.352 --> 15:21.552
Come on.

15:21.554 --> 15:23.755
(footsteps shuffle)

15:23.757 --> 15:25.590
Gimme your hand. Okay.

15:27.494 --> 15:28.959
- (chuckles)

15:28.995 --> 15:31.028
Malik: The brownings own
100 acres up here.

15:31.097 --> 15:32.963
Doesn't look inhabited at all.

15:32.999 --> 15:35.233
Donovan: Yeah, no sign
of camping or squatting.

15:35.235 --> 15:37.368
- What would you even
do up here?

15:37.503 --> 15:38.903
- Swim?

15:38.972 --> 15:41.039
- Ha. You see a lake?
- (laughs)

15:43.677 --> 15:45.242
Smell that?

15:45.278 --> 15:48.379
- Oh, man, that is the smell
of death.

15:49.683 --> 15:51.816
(low hum of police chatter)

15:53.053 --> 15:55.319
(disgusted groans and exhales)

15:55.322 --> 15:57.188
(footsteps crunch)

15:58.525 --> 16:00.525
(sighs)

16:00.660 --> 16:03.594
- It's a feral hog,
judging by the tusks.

